      <h2>Spot Me Learns Your Form</h2>
      <p class="pagetext">First, Spot Me uses the Kinect’s API to read in the Skeleton Data from the user. It loads, and modifies this data into a usable format. The data is fed into a Support Vector Machine (SVM), with a linear kernel. This was chosen as with the high degree of dimensions, the data is generally linearly separable. The SVM classifies the skeleton’s position into what kind of form it is, and outputs the appropriate message. Through continuing use of the application, which adds more training data, the SVM will build a better picture of the user’s form, and output more accurate and reliable data. </p>
